12.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Keep it in a guild context, not an open pickup group/raid.</span><hr size=1> If someone is camping a mob for a class-specific item/spell (ie for Lodizal, a melee camping the belt/map, a wizard camping for Suntrike, shaman for Malo/Torpor, etc), then by all means the item/spell should go to that person.  That should be obvious to all the folks coming to help out.  But, that's not the scenerio that was initially brought up in this thread.  The wizard in question was camping Lodizal because they wanted a high-plat sellable item to fund what they wanted.  In that situation, it's foolish and selfish for the wizard to camp him with the expectation that their guild will allow them a &quot;finder's fee&quot; of first choice of loot, especially when someone in the guild could benefit immediately from the item.  Remember, the important context here is *guild* -- this is not a random grouping or pick-up raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udarusgray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>darus gray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 3:41:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24512.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How would a melee neccessarily benifit more?</span><hr size=1> Everyone keeps saying the melee would benefit from the drops while the wizard is just too greedy to want to sell it? What do you think the wizard, probably, will do with the money? They, most likely, won't be hoarding it away for the shear joy of having lots of pp. They will, probably, upgrade their gear and then this upgrade could also help the guild. How is it selfish to assume your guild would reward you for waiting for Lodi to pop? Helping your guild should be an important priority, but shouldn't the guild also be looking out for the wizard in question as well? Aren't melees, that will wear it, more selfish if they disregard the time and effort put into the camp by the wizard and demand that she could not roll on Lodi shield pieces even though their effort was minimal compared to hers? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udumeshuhlbelk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dumesh UhlBelk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 1:27:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24512.topic&index=71>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/w/i/wilsonua/DumStare.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How would a melee neccessarily benifit more?</span><hr size=1> Amen Darus.  As a player that has camped several spawns like Lodizal, I can say that it is a serious sacrifice.  Any player that undertakes that effort should have the first pick of the loot with the rest awarded/rolled on in the usual manner.  At the very least the player who camps Lodi should be guaranteed one item even if not one of their chosing.  If a ranger, tank, shaman, or anyone else in the guild wants a lodi shield, then they can camp Lodizal the same way the wizard in this example did.<br>
<br>
For the record, Lodizal has not appeared during times that I have camped him.  However, as an officer in my guild, I have allowed the person camping Lodi his choice of the drops when we come to take out Lodi.  The rest has been assigned/rolled on in the normal way for our guild.  This system works well and helps to ensure that we almost always have someone interested in Lodizal to be camping it.  There is no shortage of Lodi shields in my guild. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2"><b>Korak Sarathai - 59 Barbarian Myrmidon - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2"><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugladoitor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladoitor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 1:48:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24512.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Gladoitor/thumbnails/Sig+pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How would a melee neccessarily benifit more?</span><hr size=1> Lodizal dont drop any of the spells listed.<br>
