<br>
THAT is the main reason that NBG is a good thing in a guild situation, if someone gets something of value you see them on raids using the item, you know that the person isn't just using the guild to fill their RL bank account.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, when items are given to guildees for the express interest of selling them, there is NO accountability and they can easily explain reasons around why it disappeared with little guild improving stuiff replacing it(&quot;Oh, I was drunk that night and sold it for 2k according to my log&quot;).<br>
<br>
If you want to sell an item for the express interest of improving your own equipment on a guild raid, bring up the idea to an officer - tell them what you would plan to get with the cash from the sale, and let them handle the sale of the cash item and the purchase of the new item. Especially with the new bazaar functions, there is no excuse for them to be unwilling to fundraise the plat with extra items - and you as the one who wants the item being saved for can check the bazaar occasionally for one to show up for them to buy for you.<br>
<br>
If your guild doesn't use a guildbank for coffins, peridots, spells, epic items, resist jewelry, etc. you do not want to be raiding with the guild - every class finds itself short of cash for something that would help it alot at some point in time, and that is what a family helps with in RL(and guess what the closest equivalent in EQ should be...) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uslyydaugg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slyy Daugg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 10:08:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24512.topic&index=74>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Quote:<br>
